ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: yes, I would. It was a really good course overall.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Changed the way I think of music and the world. Also the first musicology class I ever enjoyed.

This course raised (and aptly grappled with) a lot of very interesting and important issues in the field, including some crucial self-reflective ones--a really worthwhile course. I think the most striking takeaway for me was learning about the legacy of Nazi ideology as it affected American musicology.

This course presented varied and important perspectives on the music of Nazi Germany (and related issues) that can potentially be methodologically useful to work in other genres. The practice of writing AMS-length abstracts for our final papers was also particularly welcome and helpful.
